                    <h2 id="endpoints-POSTapi-remote-sftp-auth">Authenticate a set of credentials and return the associated server details
for a SFTP connection on the daemon. This supports both public key and password
based credentials.</h2>

<p>
</p>



<span id="example-requests-POSTapi-remote-sftp-auth">
<blockquote>Example request:</blockquote>


<div class="bash-example">
    <pre><code class="language-bash">curl --request POST \
    "http://hydrodactyl.test/api/remote/sftp/auth" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"type\": \"password\",
    \"username\": \"architecto\",
    \"password\": \"|]|{+-\"
}"
</code></pre></div>


<div class="javascript-example">
    <pre><code class="language-javascript">const url = new URL(
    "http://hydrodactyl.test/api/remote/sftp/auth"
);

