                    <h2 id="endpoints-POSTapi-remote-backups--backup--restore">Handles toggling the restoration status of a server. The server status field should be
set back to null, even if the restoration failed. This is not an unsolvable state for
the server, and the user can keep trying to restore, or just use the reinstall button.</h2>

<p>
</p>

<p>The only thing the successful field does is update the entry value for the audit logs
table tracking for this restoration.</p>

